cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a method for improving the performance of deep learning based computer vision tasks by utilizing rotation-invariant features. The paper evaluates the proposed method on face detection and robotic grasp detection tasks, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also utilizes deep neural networks (cs.LG) and proposes a new module for training and utilizing rotation-invariant features (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses data-driven features (cs.NE) instead of hand-crafted features. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV, followed by cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
